tip.text: The food is decent and please come with lower expectations. I think the reviews of this place are overrated. And the popular Roast Iced Tea is essentially iced tea with lychee syrup. Nuff said.

location.state: กรุงเทพมหานคร
formattedAddress: กรุงเทพมหานคร 10110

tip.text: My favourite city in Japan! It is easy to navigate here (grid system), has great weather in May while the rest of Japan was heating up, and has half the crowd of Tokyo.
Nothing special about the traditional dessert here. Most people are here for a taste of the past. Worth a visit if you're in the vicinity!

Ordered the tempura soba and it was great! Soup and soba were tasty (that's a given) but wasn't expecting the tempura to be just as good! Crispy batter and fresh prawns. Nth can beat that combination!
Was skeptical reading reviews that this place has the best katsu don and turned out these people were not lying! The panko was different - almost tasted like crumbled cream crackers. Awesome meal!
One of the best meals in Tokyo! The pork belly set was phenomenal and the miso was really smoky and rich. A hearty good meal especially on a cold day.

venue.name: Ohitsuzen Tanbo (おひつ膳 田んぼ 代々木本店)

tip.text: Was disappointed with the hot latte and portion. You won't miss much if you skip this place.

venue.name: 十勝豚丼 いっぴん ステラプレイス店

tip.text: Everyone raves about the ricotta hotcakes but the dish that wowed my hubby and I was the corn fritters. The combination with bacon strips and diced avocado made it incredible. Got to try it!

location.crossStreet: 東急プラザ 表参道原宿 7F

tip.text: Amazing interior! Good coffee and food.
Love the hotcakes! The portion is huge though.
Beautiful place to bring a date.. Love the aged duck and caramelised egg plant!
Incredible margherita pizza! Very surprised by the standard of the desserts! Got to try the tiramisu!

venue.name: 日勝生加賀屋 Kagaya Taipei

tip.text: Pork belly burger! Yum! And the fries are fresh! That's the best part for me.

formattedAddress: #04-49, Beauty World Centre Food Centre (144 Upper Bukit Timah Rd.)

tip.text: White bee hoon with chilli sauce! Order a large portion to share if you are in a group though anyone can easily polish off a small plate cos it's so yummy!

venue.name: You Huak Restaurant (Sembawang White Beehoon 三巴旺白米粉)

tip.text: A-B-C grilled cheese sandwich was pretty good! Didn't expect apple, bacon and cheese to go well at all..

tip.text: The baked beans are to die for!
Heavenly fresh apam and putu mayam!
